Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.67,0:00:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And so each one represents a level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.75,0:00:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We first presented the levels of human consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.11,0:00:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that integrity, the major one to worry about is 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get over 200, the rest is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People are already worrying about what their level of consciousness is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.26,0:01:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing of any concern is whether you're over 200 or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.60,0:01:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because the rest has a thousand karmic propensities
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.24,0:01:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and has to do with motivation, has to do with a multitude of factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.58,0:01:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention, however, drives you through the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.06,0:01:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the work that's involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.36,0:01:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lifetime, it was extraordinary, the amount of work at times,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.70,0:01:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the other times, extraordinary in that they were spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.60,0:01:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and not preceded by any work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.56,0:01:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no predictable cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.65,0:01:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A person says, I've been doing these mudras,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.65,0:01:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been doing these hand positions,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.53,0:01:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been doing these breathing exercises,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.11,0:01:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been doing the meditating, and I'm not getting anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.43,0:01:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, instantly his consciousness level just jumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.63,0:02:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He was trying to artificially control, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.09,0:02:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Artificially control your level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.41,0:02:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of just letting it be that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.13,0:02:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which is kindly, considerate, humorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.74,0:02:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,See the humor in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.79,0:02:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people cry in agony all the way to the chopping block.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, me, they're chopping my head off today, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy come, easy go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As an old head chopper, I was telling them,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.54,0:02:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only going to hurt for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only going to hurt for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.08,0:02:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.60,0:02:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.73,0:02:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just stated is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.27,0:03:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.33,0:03:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In one second, no more pain, no more suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.61,0:03:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a body and this dopey head rolling around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.99,0:03:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The French peasants are jumping up and down with glee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.11,0:03:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they call them peasants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.96,0:03:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the French aristocracy thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.38,0:03:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Peasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one then is a way of perceiving the world, perceiving yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.30,0:03:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with a certain level of energy and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.38,0:03:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the degree to which the kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.56,0:03:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,has become dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.88,0:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, there's the classic chakra system,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.52,0:03:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the spiritual energy is envisioned as flowing up the chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Which again, is really analogous rather than a literality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.46,0:04:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever measured it, except us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to say, nobody ever measured it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.61,0:04:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I realized we're measuring it all the time, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.93,0:04:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the level of consciousness, then, is what the number denotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.48,0:04:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not mean better than.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.26,0:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what appeals to you, at a given time in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,may be quite different than what appeals to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.52,0:04:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and becomes meaningless later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.73,0:04:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the spiritual teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.68,0:04:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with the most popular impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.26,0:04:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are those that probably calibrate in the mid-200s,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the 700s.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.85,0:04:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We go, ooh and ahh at 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the people who teach goodwill,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.41,0:04:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.36,0:04:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I'm a fan of the Boy Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Boy and Girl Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Scouts calibrate around 460, or somewhere around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.62,0:05:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scouts calibrate around over 450,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.62,0:05:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,460,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.54,0:05:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,455.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scouts calibrate at 455.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of going all the way to India and seeking Guru Ba-Ba-Drum-Drum,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I suggest you join the Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.57,0:05:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scouts are at 455,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.57,0:05:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Guru who used to be high, is now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, at 140,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.37,0:05:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and sleeps with everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.40,0:05:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,have holy sex, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.26,0:05:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that people can sell themselves, hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.92,0:05:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, an integrous teaching of a lower number.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.42,0:05:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you see often attracts people to more advanced teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the glamour of the more advanced teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.42,0:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality, like anything else, can become a glamour,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:05:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,like popularity, like money, like titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.93,0:06:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just glamourized.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.93,0:06:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he calibrates at 70 to 95.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.93,0:06:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Except you don't know what the hell he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.00,0:06:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not too helpful if you don't know what the person means.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.00,0:06:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Ramana Maharishi says,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.00,0:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in lamenting the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or intervening, or trying to do something about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true in the level 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.22,0:06:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But it'd be a spiritual error not to do something to help the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.76,0:06:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're calibrating at 260.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.76,0:06:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have your choice between service towards others or selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The world you see doesn't even exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.17,0:06:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is so at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not so at 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Katrina, or Kachina, or whatever the name of that horror hurricane was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,tornado, whatever that thing was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.65,0:06:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,knocked down a zillion people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.65,0:06:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.35,0:07:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So your perception of it then is reflection of your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you feel called to do depends on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot be false to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be true to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.44,0:07:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as a fellow human.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.44,0:07:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do what I can to be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that's what you're called upon to do at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're at a different level,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.92,0:07:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see this karmic consequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a group karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing to do with individuals or causality or anything like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.92,0:07:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can do nothing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.53,0:07:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not so until it's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.53,0:07:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not so until it's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.53,0:07:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't be false to ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.53,0:07:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own self be true means,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.53,0:07:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,however you see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.53,0:07:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is what your obligation is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So our karmic obligation is dependent on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.72,0:07:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,our culpability
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.72,0:07:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and responsibility are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.72,0:07:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.72,0:07:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:07:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility is a karmic given.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take somebody's life, you owe a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.45,0:08:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's independent of culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.45,0:08:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability has to do with the degree of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If the child pulls out a gun from his parents' dresser drawer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and shoots somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,his culpability is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.55,0:08:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.55,0:08:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And he will have to pay back the life in another life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.55,0:08:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.96,0:08:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He owes a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically, you owe a life because you took a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.64,0:08:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the culpability may be zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.73,0:08:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And even the courts recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.73,0:08:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the degree of responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.73,0:08:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the imbecile, the so-called retarded person, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is seen to be operating under impaired responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.73,0:08:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, their culpability is less.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.73,0:08:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they are still accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.73,0:08:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you make a pledge, you're accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is what you pledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.02,0:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,then this is what you give
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:08:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,if you leave that particular group.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the oath you took.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.42,0:09:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tried to include some,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.42,0:09:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the most easily recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some more popular,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which I have on another list,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.42,0:09:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,currently alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are popularizers of spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.42,0:09:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Popularizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.42,0:09:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often they're a good place to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.42,0:09:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they get you excited about the whole subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give you a place to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.87,0:09:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are extremely well known, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.87,0:09:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Pot and Jelly, 715.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you pronounce his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.12,0:09:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Patanjali or Pot and Jelly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.17,0:09:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody here knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.82,0:09:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We in Dyer calls them Pot and Jelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.82,0:09:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was thinking of them as Patanjali.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.82,0:09:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.85,0:10:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we see Father Pio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.04,0:10:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the ways he exhibited the cities was
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by location.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.26,0:10:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To be several places at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.26,0:10:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course that would sound very odd to a skeptic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.15,0:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the skeptic dictionary didn't approve of Father Pio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because such a thing is beyond linear probability.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.44,0:10:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond linear probability.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been two places at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.63,0:10:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can disappear time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.63,0:10:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.63,0:10:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can disappear distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.63,0:10:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,By letting go, resisting the experiencing of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.63,0:10:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to do it routinely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.92,0:10:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Driving from Phoenix to Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.59,0:10:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is very boring after you've done it a couple hundred times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And by letting go, resisting the subjective experiencing of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.59,0:11:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Which you do continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.62,0:11:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But you feel the experiencing of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.62,0:11:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you let go, resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're impatient to get to Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's late at night, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.75,0:11:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you constantly let go, resisting the experiencing of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.75,0:11:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,time disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.75,0:11:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden within a minute you're in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.97,0:11:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you leave Phoenix at 10.01 and at 10.03 you're in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.97,0:11:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjective experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to do it routinely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can use these kind of techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.97,0:11:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Of anything that you find onerous or difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.10,0:11:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of resisting of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the subjective experiencing of time itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.10,0:11:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even let go of resisting your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.10,0:11:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one you can save.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.87,0:12:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting your own experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.87,0:12:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the delusion is, if you don't keep recreating it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.64,0:12:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what it means that the self is reborn every split second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That unless you intend the continuation of your own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That you, what you think is the you, will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstatically to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.26,0:12:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.26,0:12:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so you can disappear time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.26,0:12:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can see you can disappear the resistance to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is your oyster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you want you can let go of resisting having money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.90,0:12:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.90,0:12:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting having money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.73,0:12:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting the wanting to have money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.73,0:12:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Be crazy to have money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:12:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Go insane to have money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.24,0:13:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.33,0:13:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally you say, no one needs money, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.59,0:13:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So who needs it anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.59,0:13:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You let go of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.59,0:13:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly your aunt leaves you a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell this story in the book about Greta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I told Greta?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.20,0:13:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who came over from Ireland without a nickel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how far she got in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.26,0:13:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Went to work for one of the most famous rich families in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lived in the Locust Valley around where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.32,0:13:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And they hired her as a bookkeeper, as a housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.32,0:13:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And Greta was so integrous and so dedicated to the family and the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.93,0:13:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I told this story before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.06,0:13:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That at dinner time the old man would give her tips on the stock market.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.12,0:13:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your hundred dollars Greta and invest it in a Zanza.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.24,0:13:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It would triple within a week, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.24,0:13:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it was insider training, illegal nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I had somebody come to me one time and he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, give me $10,000 and I'll make it go up ten times within 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.24,0:14:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I know what this company is going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.56,0:14:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pure and poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.91,0:14:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do with my teachers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So at each level you get attracted to certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.16,0:14:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So which teacher is meaningful to you is many factors including many unknown karmic factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.16,0:14:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that Father Pugh represents first of all the background of Catholicism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.45,0:14:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So some of the teachers represent the emergence and most mystics emerge beyond many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:14:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A large number that are well known to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.45,0:15:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Emerged out of various religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.45,0:15:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest level of awareness is always the mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.60,0:15:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though the mystic is a member of a certain religious organization or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.96,0:15:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic who shoots over a level 600 does so by becoming the truth from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.53,0:15:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And may or may not hang around the religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.88,0:15:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In which this arose later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.88,0:15:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's merely the setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's mystics in every religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Every major religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic is one in whom who has followed the evolution of consciousness such as we've described.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the truth shines forth of its own radiance from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.33,0:15:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not acquired as a book learning or a memorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with liturgy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with ecclesiastic approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.46,0:16:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with an inner awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have done severe physical exertion to the point of exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.61,0:16:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I give the example I've given.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan has had the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.61,0:16:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You push yourself to the absolute limit beyond which you cannot go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.61,0:16:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be an endeavor such as walking barefoot across the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.84,0:16:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.84,0:16:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You push yourself to the limit beyond which you cannot go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you refuse the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.02,0:16:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you shoot past the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.88,0:16:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you move into the incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.88,0:16:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what I call the Roger Bannister effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.24,0:16:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You push the human endurance past to the level that science says you cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.24,0:16:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You refuse with an iron like savage will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:16:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when it's time to get yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The time to get yang is when you run up the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.24,0:17:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You run up against the I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when you crash through the I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.40,0:17:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly you're in a different dimension which is effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.43,0:17:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All the boxes that you couldn't lift anymore are now weightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember being in that warehouse exhausted after 12 hours of work and that heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot lift another box.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was like gritting your teeth and all of a sudden it was effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The body was like feather.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The boxes lifted themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.48,0:17:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And dawn, it went all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.48,0:17:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn was there and they said, you haven't been to bed yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.48,0:17:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The same happens when you go into a state of ecstasy where you can dance effortlessly hour after hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.56,0:17:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And those cities are available to any spiritual student.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.69,0:18:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They arise as an opportunity to exceed the limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.13,0:18:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the limitation is the belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.13,0:18:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're only subject to what you hold in mind, then you have a belief that you're limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.45,0:18:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That you can only lift so many boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.45,0:18:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That you've been so many hours without food.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.45,0:18:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been so many hours without water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it's not physically possible to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is possible to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not you as a person, but your beingness can go on because your beingness is unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.16,0:18:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It can keep on working and working and working.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are things we hear about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.16,0:18:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio's miraculous things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We hear about the great saint, Saint Patrick, that launched Christianity in Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, he's very famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.83,0:18:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And corned beef and cabbage was named that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.18,0:19:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yogananda is extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.18,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Autobiography of a yoga.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has a place started in California.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.31,0:19:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the other teachers come from other cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're not familiar with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.50,0:19:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,However, their writings are extremely familiar to many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.69,0:19:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Yogananda himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was a fun guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And he used to take these orange hats and throw them in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.95,0:19:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,During the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there would be a crowd around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.08,0:19:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the crowd knew that his energy was in the orange hats.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So he had a pile of orange hats.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.11,0:19:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd wear one for five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he'd throw it in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody would take it home because they knew his energy was in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,His energy at that time was 655.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.11,0:19:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But met Yogananda anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.32,0:19:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:20:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I'm trying to say is the spiritual evolution is progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It should bring you into progressive joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.92,0:20:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the same thing as piety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.05,0:20:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Piety and saintliness is a very nice thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.05,0:20:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when you're on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.37,0:20:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And the robes sway nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.37,0:20:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And your sandals go clip-clop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now those are distortions of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because spiritual integrity is very, very, normally, honestly, that which is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.54,0:20:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to pretend to be anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.54,0:20:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It is exactly what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.54,0:20:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's so completely satisfied with that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.54,0:20:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to imitate that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.54,0:20:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Which it is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.54,0:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So one thing we'd say about these teachers, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they all represent an intrinsic integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.64,0:21:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with nothing to gain, nothing to sell, no desire to control anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.08,0:21:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha recommended enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.18,0:21:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as a way to avoid the pain of reincarnation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.18,0:21:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and going through the pain and misery of humanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.18,0:21:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting born and dying, sickness, old age, poverty and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.33,0:21:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm recommended too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.94,0:21:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at a certain point you don't care about sickness, old age, poverty and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.94,0:21:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got an apple for dinner, what more do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a cot to sleep on, there's a wooden box.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only thing is the big desert centipedes do crawl around
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.10,0:21:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and give you a little heebie-jeebies once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.10,0:21:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But other than that, poverty is perfectly fine, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.10,0:21:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever you need arises out of the occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.10,0:21:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It arises not as a matter of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It emerges as a consequence of the occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.10,0:22:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to stop now so that we have more to talk about later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.10,0:22:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to make the afternoon a little shorter as far as the lecture goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.29,0:22:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have more time for questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.58,0:22:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to see us eventually move into workshops
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.64,0:22:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that are a lot of interaction with the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.64,0:22:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of, you know, it grabs you to, you want me to explain more about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.64,0:22:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.64,0:22:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.64,0:22:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In which we become more spontaneously interactive with each other, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.64,0:22:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And get away from this artificiality that the teacher up there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.64,0:22:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and us down here, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's actually all of us here, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.64,0:22:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd really like people to, I'd really, the best way I'd like to teach
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.64,0:22:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would be to wander through the audience and people spontaneously bring up
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.64,0:22:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what is coming up in the field, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.64,0:22:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you people are the field and all these heads here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.64,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are picking up the thoughts and the feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:22:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's, you know, the teacher is what's sitting in the chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.64,0:23:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher, this is just the responder to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.64,0:23:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way I'd like to teach is wander through the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.64,0:23:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and people just pop up with whatever they got and they answer back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.64,0:23:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That will drive Robert crazy, but the man in the wall says the mechanics of that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.71,0:23:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are difficult and the TV people, of course, they also say that's difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle the mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.71,0:23:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus didn't have that problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.71,0:23:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The great saints of old didn't have to get focused on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.71,0:23:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and turn up the volume on the recorder, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.77,0:23:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But they served a different function.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.77,0:23:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that you see the speed of spiritual evolution is very rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.77,0:23:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And one is mass media, one is people here by the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.77,0:23:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That which was only heard by a dozen favorite people years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.87,0:23:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's available to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.87,0:24:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll conclude with this finality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.87,0:24:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances of becoming enlightened today are over 1,000 times greater than in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.87,0:24:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 1,000 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.87,0:24:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just confirm that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.87,0:24:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 1,000 times. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.51,0:24:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can get off the excuse that it's very, very rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.67,0:24:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore it doesn't apply to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.28,0:24:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay for me to not be enlightened because it hardly ever happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.28,0:24:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is now. Get busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.72,0:24:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all here because we're all here because we're all here because we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.11,0:25:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Serious spiritual work, it's hard to remain serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.57,0:25:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you're constantly confronted by absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.57,0:25:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.83,0:25:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception versus essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.83,0:25:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you put the two together, you get humor, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.69,0:25:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. Where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.57,0:25:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.69,0:25:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Integra spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.88,0:25:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's great popularization of spiritual fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.68,0:25:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the naive students and people who are interested in spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.68,0:25:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,think that's what spirituality is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.68,0:25:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, best sellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.68,0:25:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing that I don't like about them is they don't make it clear that it's fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.26,0:26:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And they state it as though it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.64,0:26:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly a saint appears next to you, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.64,0:26:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's, you know, it's a writer's fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.77,0:26:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.77,0:26:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not the reincarnation of St. Patrick or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.41,0:26:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's all kinds of spiritual fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.41,0:26:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And people get it confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.41,0:26:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And the spiritual fiction is also the lure for the child within
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.41,0:26:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who likes the imaginative and the fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.41,0:26:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more fantastic the climb, the bigger the sales, you'll notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.57,0:26:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus and Mary were married and their children became the aristocracy of France
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.63,0:26:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and all such BS.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.40,0:26:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble is the naive seeker considers that truth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.40,0:26:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's an interesting book out called Odd Gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.40,0:26:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Odd Gods by James Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.40,0:26:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Odd Gods and the Cult Phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.40,0:26:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pretty thick book.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.49,0:26:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing I like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.49,0:27:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That is funny, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.49,0:27:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a pretty thick book, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.65,0:27:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Books of spiritual truth are slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.00,0:27:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What I like about it is he gives you many examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.77,0:27:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the examples, you get the drift of it, how it comes about.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.77,0:27:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see what it attracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.77,0:27:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It attracts the innocent child with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.77,0:27:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Within us who like magic and fantasy and the fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.77,0:27:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So many things that are called, considered by the populace, the spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.77,0:27:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are really, you know, the fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.77,0:27:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Harry Potter books, at least, you know, it's clear from the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.77,0:27:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you're talking about a trueness story.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.77,0:27:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But these books, you know, I know that people take it serious
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.00,0:27:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because some highly intelligent people write me long dissertations about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.00,0:27:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.03,0:27:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,About what's the one with the painting from my...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.28,0:27:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Da Vinci.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.44,0:28:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Da Vinci, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.44,0:28:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No end of the Da Vinci crap I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.44,0:28:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Emails and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.44,0:28:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, no end, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.79,0:28:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why I calibrated some of it for the book
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.79,0:28:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because I want to point out to people there's spiritual fiction
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.79,0:28:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's spiritual reality, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.79,0:28:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality doesn't sound as appealing as the fantasy and the fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.79,0:28:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Which appeals to the romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.79,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So within us all is the child and the child's curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.79,0:28:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the child's naivety, impressionability, and people become misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.85,0:28:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So where were we on the slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.85,0:28:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We were someplace or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.85,0:28:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.88,0:28:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we wanted to go over those.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.98,0:28:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,These, of course, this is 144, plus I got another 20 here,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.17,0:28:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which I've lost someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.27,0:28:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They're more contemporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.68,0:28:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But this should do, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.68,0:29:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You just take one and follow it through,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.35,0:29:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and that'll take you to 605,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.35,0:29:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't need another book until you get past 605.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.48,0:29:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you just do the one thing consistently.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.48,0:29:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the thing, the magic of spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.57,0:29:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.57,0:29:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sincerity, of course, integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.70,0:29:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But the consistency with which you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.96,0:29:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could say, well, I heard, you know, from the doc the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.96,0:29:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you just let go, resisting, experiencing the passage of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.99,0:29:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you go outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.99,0:29:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But it may take a while to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.99,0:29:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You may continually do it and continually do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.31,0:29:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean the first time you do it, it's going to work this fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.31,0:29:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you persist in it, let go resisting the passage of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.53,0:29:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let go resisting it, let go resisting the passage of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.53,0:29:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let go resisting it, let go resenting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.53,0:30:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you go outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.52,0:30:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And within no time at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.07,0:30:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you find yourself back in Sedona on the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.07,0:30:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of these things take a certain persistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.74,0:30:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because there's a certain karmic momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.74,0:30:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't call it, you're not determined by karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.74,0:30:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I call them propensities,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.74,0:30:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which you inherit once you have an etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.92,0:30:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is your spiritual history encapsulated, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.92,0:30:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in a vibrational form,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.92,0:30:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is a propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.92,0:30:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not predetermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.92,0:30:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma doesn't mean predetermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.08,0:30:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma means propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.31,0:30:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the evolution of consciousness is over very long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.53,0:30:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Very long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.72,0:31:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the evolution of one's consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.00,0:31:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.12,0:31:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain point, as I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.12,0:31:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you remember previous lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.12,0:31:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it may happen spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.12,0:31:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or there's various techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.57,0:31:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The only time I think it's really important,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.57,0:31:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,past life recall,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.57,0:31:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is if you are stuck with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.73,0:31:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say the way to get out of a stuckness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.73,0:31:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is see what's happening in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.73,0:31:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say you're the victim of,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.73,0:31:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or picture yourself as the victim of,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.12,0:31:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what you pray for is the one within you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.12,0:31:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who did that to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.60,0:31:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother praying for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.60,0:31:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.25,0:31:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,People are always cheating me,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.25,0:31:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always getting, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.25,0:31:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I get them home and there's only ten eggs in the carton.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.00,0:31:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're always being shortchanged,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.00,0:31:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and always being taken advantage of by others,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.00,0:32:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then what you pray for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.00,0:32:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the one in you who shortchanges others.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.00,0:32:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Always give it a 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.10,0:32:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Always presume that all the stuff in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.74,0:32:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want is the karmic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.74,0:32:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of you having done it to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.74,0:32:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.16,0:32:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not asking you to believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.16,0:32:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just asking you to try it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.16,0:32:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.64,0:32:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's rude to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.64,0:32:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so, now you don't recall
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.64,0:32:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the one in you who's rude to others,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.64,0:32:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for one thing you don't recall that lifetime maybe,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.80,0:32:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but the other thing you don't realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.80,0:32:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we collectively inherit
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.80,0:32:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.18,0:32:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Carol Young was correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.18,0:32:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a collective unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.18,0:32:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so even though you personally don't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.18,0:32:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,such a belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.18,0:32:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,nevertheless, you live in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.18,0:33:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you're getting programmed constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.18,0:33:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I never in my life believed in osteoporosis
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.40,0:33:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,affecting myself or men in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.40,0:33:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was for little old ladies bent over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.40,0:33:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, if you're only subject
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.05,0:33:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to what you hold in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.12,0:33:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,then how can you get osteoporosis
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.12,0:33:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you believed in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.63,0:33:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I personally never believed in it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.63,0:33:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as being the potential to afflict
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.63,0:33:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this person here,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.63,0:33:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who was all very vigorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.04,0:33:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a star dancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.04,0:33:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.04,0:33:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a star dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.04,0:33:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I could dance any dance, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.04,0:33:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That came out of a lifetime too once.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.04,0:33:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.00,0:33:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I don't remember ever believing in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.07,0:33:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but you sat through a TV commercial
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.10,0:33:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all about osteoporosis
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.10,0:33:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and taking this, that, and the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.10,0:33:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked it up, you picked it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.10,0:34:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so just presume
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.23,0:34:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever is coming down in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.23,0:34:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you picked up somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.45,0:34:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it so?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.00,0:34:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how do things come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.86,0:34:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They come about by the power of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.86,0:34:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.86,0:34:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as a belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.73,0:34:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the physical body is incapable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.73,0:34:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of experiencing its own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.04,0:34:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because of the senses
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.04,0:34:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're aware of what goes on in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.04,0:34:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not experiencing the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.04,0:34:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you're experiencing the sensations of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.04,0:34:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know the body is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.33,0:34:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.33,0:34:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're not even experiencing the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.33,0:34:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're experiencing the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.33,0:34:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the Buddha called the brain a sense organ.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.47,0:34:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the feelings have no capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.47,0:34:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.53,0:34:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because there's something greater
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.53,0:34:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,than the feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.60,0:34:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they can be experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.60,0:35:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is in consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.20,0:35:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is insentient.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.47,0:35:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the body cannot experience anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.33,0:35:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is not capable of experiencing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.33,0:35:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience is of a different dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.33,0:35:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.33,0:35:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is not able to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.45,0:35:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,even that it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.45,0:35:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.87,0:35:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And feelings are then,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.87,0:35:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's an awareness of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.87,0:35:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind can't know what it's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.25,0:35:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.96,0:35:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is in something greater than itself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.96,0:35:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which illuminates what the mind is thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.96,0:35:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,called consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.96,0:35:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are then is the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.21,0:35:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all the sequence occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.21,0:35:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is held in mind then begins to manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.30,0:35:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,within the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.30,0:35:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I develop osteoporosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.56,0:35:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I have picked it up somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.75,0:35:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in our culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.75,0:36:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I've picked it up from the collective mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.75,0:36:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'm holding it from some previous lifetime, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.22,0:36:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to get unhooked from some karmic probability
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.35,0:36:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or potentiality likelihood,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.38,0:36:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if it keeps recurring in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.38,0:36:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,just give it an okay that it's likely
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.38,0:36:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.15,0:36:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore do a 180 on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.40,0:36:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's shortchanging you,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.79,0:36:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to apologize
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.82,0:36:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask for forgiveness for the one in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.82,0:36:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.82,0:36:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I picked up an identification
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.82,0:36:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with the collective,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.82,0:36:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one who cheats others is part of you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.82,0:36:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the collective unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.30,0:36:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the fact you identify yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.30,0:36:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.30,0:36:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wham!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.30,0:36:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You just pulled in the entire karma
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.30,0:36:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of being human.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.26,0:36:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the personal experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.36,0:36:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the personal past life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.55,0:37:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be very, very specific,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.55,0:37:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way, very specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.55,0:37:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you learn how to rerun them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.74,0:37:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it's amazing how specific they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.74,0:37:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You see exactly what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.74,0:37:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the exact why of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.74,0:37:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you're empowered to undo of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.74,0:37:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,undo of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.74,0:37:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.22,0:37:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know whether this, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.67,0:37:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,share any past lives with you at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.67,0:37:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.67,0:37:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.89,0:37:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.89,0:37:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was Mr. Clubfoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.99,0:37:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was too inhibited.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.02,0:37:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And one time in sort of a high state,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.02,0:37:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly recalled a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.02,0:37:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as a temple dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.34,0:37:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly I could dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.63,0:37:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly I became an expert dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.63,0:37:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I could dance any kind of dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.63,0:37:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.63,0:37:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretive, ballet, disco,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.72,0:37:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,western.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.72,0:37:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was president of the country western dance club,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.04,0:38:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I was a dancing fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.04,0:38:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So once I learned how to dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.07,0:38:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this frustration of my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.07,0:38:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I went dancing all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.07,0:38:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So undoing the one karmic thing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.64,0:38:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,unleashed the capacity to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.64,0:38:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So how would you have the talent
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.64,0:38:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to do all that kind of dancing?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.64,0:38:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you get the talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.64,0:38:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was a very good temple dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.64,0:38:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a very excellent temple dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.64,0:38:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can still do temple dancing for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.71,0:38:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.84,0:38:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it came out of that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.84,0:38:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So then once you're freed of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.84,0:38:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell right away
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.84,0:38:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you just got freed of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.84,0:38:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You just like know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.84,0:38:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.87,0:38:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll tell you a few lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.87,0:38:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,once in a while just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.87,0:38:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the most important one.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.41,0:38:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the circumstances in which I recall it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.75,0:38:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shackled to oars.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.75,0:39:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a slave on a slave ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.84,0:39:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And shackled with chains to the oar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.48,0:39:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And this guy who sets the beat,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.64,0:39:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I wasn't able to keep up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.64,0:39:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he came over and started beating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.08,0:39:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's beating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.08,0:39:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll never forget the smell of that galley.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.08,0:39:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,God, it stunk because
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.08,0:39:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you got water running down behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.08,0:39:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're chained, you see, to this bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.08,0:39:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.08,0:39:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,relieves themselves and the water
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.08,0:39:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,rushes in from the sea and washes it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.47,0:39:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I reached the point of absolute exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.47,0:39:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.47,0:39:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was holding on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.47,0:39:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding on, holding on, holding on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.66,0:39:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And this guy was never going to stop beating on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.69,0:39:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly it came to me out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.69,0:39:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in just that lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.27,0:39:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm not a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.27,0:39:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.27,0:39:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I let go of life, my physical life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.27,0:40:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly went into spirit and I was free.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.62,0:40:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot be enslaved because that which I am
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.62,0:40:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond the physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.62,0:40:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And that knowingness came to me in that instant
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.62,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.42,0:40:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And there I was, free
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.42,0:40:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that pain and suffering and agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.42,0:40:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What a happy spirit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.42,0:40:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Free, free, forever free.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.42,0:40:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now we're going back to the spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.58,0:40:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And so those things come to you spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.85,0:40:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.11,0:40:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're stuck with something,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.11,0:40:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,presume that there's something behind that stuckness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.11,0:40:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And with a little research,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.11,0:40:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you can sometimes find your way out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.11,0:40:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it sort of comes to you as a sudden flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.11,0:40:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, dear God,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.11,0:40:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why I'm stuck with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.11,0:40:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And dear God, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.11,0:40:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like your mudra,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.11,0:40:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,your way of being is a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.11,0:40:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask God for the miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.62,0:41:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of seeing what lies behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.62,0:41:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you get a vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.62,0:41:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you get a rerun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.62,0:41:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's just a remark somebody says.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.62,0:41:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I got an insight into something that came up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.62,0:41:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just at lunchtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.62,0:41:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It just came up spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.62,0:41:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, I can see why that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.62,0:41:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.62,0:41:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not the consequence of logical thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.39,0:41:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So being receptive,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.39,0:41:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,making your life for prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.39,0:41:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very yin position,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.39,0:41:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,yin position, yin position,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.39,0:41:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you are open to divine inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.45,0:41:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like a quality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.87,0:41:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that it cannot refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.87,0:41:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.80,0:41:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it can't refuse
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.80,0:41:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the invitation when that supplication
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.80,0:41:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is at a deep level of humility
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and absolutely genuine,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.80,0:41:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.80,0:41:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the power of the yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.80,0:41:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The life, the worldly life imagines
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power all belongs to the yang,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.80,0:42:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the masculine.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.12,0:42:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the power belongs to the yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.12,0:42:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A yin by this attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.12,0:42:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,can kill a thousand men.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.12,0:42:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do to kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.15,0:42:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I stood back,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.15,0:42:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I allowed them to be themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.15,0:42:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they slaughtered each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.15,0:42:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,did they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.21,0:42:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.60,0:42:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,emphasizing the advantage of one sex or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.04,0:42:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because they both have their own intrinsic style.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.04,0:42:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Masculinity is a style,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.04,0:42:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and femininity is a style,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.04,0:42:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're of equal power,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.04,0:42:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as any man knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.04,0:42:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All she does is go,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.22,0:42:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but honey,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.22,0:42:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,wow,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.22,0:42:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,his day has just got changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.48,0:42:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Puts away the golf bags,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.48,0:42:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,gets out the lawn mower,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.31,0:42:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother-in-law is coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.31,0:43:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and look at the lawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.31,0:43:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, honey, don't be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.31,0:43:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All she did is raise an eyebrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.31,0:43:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.31,0:43:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She raised one eyebrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.79,0:43:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,she changes the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.73,0:43:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's up there pushing and trying to make it all happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.73,0:43:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and she just goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.65,0:43:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so much for my view of the masculine and the feminine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.65,0:43:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll go back to the written word here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.42,0:43:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to stop a little earlier today than usually,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.42,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're going to get more time for questions and discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.48,0:43:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was just ruminating, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.48,0:43:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to meet some of the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.12,0:43:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And Robert Monroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.12,0:43:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Monroe is the Monroe Institute,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.12,0:43:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,teaches you in all your state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.12,0:43:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can go out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.12,0:43:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I went out of the body spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.41,0:43:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,long before it was popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.41,0:43:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wrote about near-death experiences or out of body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.41,0:44:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I was in psychoanalysis at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.83,0:44:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was deathly ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.18,0:44:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, I was out there in the middle of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.31,0:44:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The complete sense of who you are is there,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.31,0:44:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,except for the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.31,0:44:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.31,0:44:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll tell you it's very boring and not too attractive looking there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.31,0:44:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, every time you're out of body,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.31,0:44:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at the physical body and you're like,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.31,0:44:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.08,0:44:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a really nothing experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.08,0:44:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But out of body, you know, you can think, feel, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.08,0:44:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All the senses are operative.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.08,0:44:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you about the time I went to the Monroe Institute
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.08,0:44:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and learned how to go out of body at will.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.08,0:44:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I docked back in the body upside down,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.08,0:44:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,180 degrees out of phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.08,0:44:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking out the back of my head at the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.08,0:44:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had to come out this way and go back in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.07,0:44:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Journeys out of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.10,0:44:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Journeys out of the body is a fun, fun book.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.10,0:44:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because nobody knew anything about such phenomena at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.48,0:45:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience or out of body was not heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.48,0:45:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And Monroe began to spontaneously experience this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.48,0:45:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would have these amorous adventures,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he'd come back in his body with his wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.48,0:45:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'd be stricken with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.48,0:45:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very funny book.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.48,0:45:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'd gotten into some lower astral realms
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.71,0:45:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and various places like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.71,0:45:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we did the Monroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.71,0:45:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and learned how to go out of body,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.71,0:45:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to come back in the body at a whistle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.71,0:45:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.71,0:45:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because people would get involved in various adventures
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.71,0:45:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in various astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.71,0:45:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you had to make sure you were safe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.71,0:45:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,before they let you out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.71,0:45:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So they would train you how to get out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.71,0:45:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you were trained at the sound of this whistle
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.71,0:45:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to come back in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.71,0:45:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how I shot back in the body
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.71,0:45:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and discovered I was upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.16,0:45:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing about Monroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.16,0:45:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,who I think is deceased now,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.35,0:45:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he had the greatest voice I ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.35,0:45:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ever get a chance to get a tape
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.35,0:45:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or something by Robert Monroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.57,0:45:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,he had a sound of intrinsic peace within his voice
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that was just amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.57,0:46:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just spoke from a level of absolute inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.73,0:46:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Really a mystical, incredible gift he had.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.83,0:46:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.83,0:46:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Muktananda I met, Monroe I met,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.17,0:46:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the others are really from different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.17,0:46:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.17,0:46:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and different times.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.17,0:46:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is probably the best known
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.24,0:46:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because of Wayne Dyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.24,0:46:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Patanjali, he calls him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.24,0:46:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio is extremely well known also.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.46,0:46:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The last pope was at 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.46,0:46:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this pope was at 565.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.46,0:46:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.62,0:46:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The last pope was 570,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.62,0:46:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a saintly beneficence towards all.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.62,0:46:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of a wholeness and oneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.62,0:46:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was, of course, quite saintly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.77,0:47:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Plotinus is also extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.77,0:47:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po, I think I spoke to you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.77,0:47:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with Huang Po,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.77,0:47:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you follow him literally,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.77,0:47:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to negate the reality of the linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.77,0:47:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we've already covered,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.87,0:47:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you will end up at the void,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.87,0:47:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.93,0:47:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the void is not where you want to end up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.93,0:47:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Many naive Buddhists,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.19,0:47:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact we get emails from,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.19,0:47:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,end up at 800,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.19,0:47:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.19,0:47:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.32,0:47:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the outcome of a belief system,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.32,0:47:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ultimate reality is nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.32,0:47:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a trap, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.53,0:47:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So he taught, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.53,0:47:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go of belief,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.53,0:47:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,any belief or attachment in the linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.53,0:47:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereby you end up in,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.53,0:47:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he presumed, in the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.53,0:47:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time he wrote it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.66,0:47:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,he was at 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.66,0:48:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And what he was talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.66,0:48:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have gotten complaints from email
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.66,0:48:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,about people who landed in the void,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.66,0:48:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.88,0:48:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the void is not the absolute state
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.88,0:48:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.88,0:48:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute state is allness, allness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.88,0:48:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that differentiates the two
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.64,0:48:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the ultimate state
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.64,0:48:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is filled and pervaded and predominant
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.77,0:48:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,predominantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.77,0:48:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,predominantly exquisite love
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.77,0:48:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of an incredible quality beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.77,0:48:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no thingness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.83,0:48:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the quality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.69,0:48:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the qualities of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.69,0:48:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a slide on that at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.30,0:48:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,After he reached that state
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.30,0:48:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in which he wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.46,0:48:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pathway of Negation,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.10,0:48:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he himself discovered the error
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.10,0:48:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and went on to 960 before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.10,0:48:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But he never wrote anything after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.10,0:48:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the last thing he wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.42,0:49:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is The Pathway of Negation at 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.55,0:49:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he himself went on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.90,0:49:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to write at those higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.44,0:49:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So he may have,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.44,0:49:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how long before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.44,0:49:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but he discovered the ultimate truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.44,0:49:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate truth calibrates at 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.51,0:49:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothingness, the void, calibrates at 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.51,0:49:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've already mentioned that,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.51,0:49:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think I explained it in the book
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.51,0:49:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that's coming out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.54,0:49:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The error of a misunderstanding Hoang Po.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.57,0:49:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Robert Powell, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.18,0:49:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.18,0:49:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All these Swamis are well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.21,0:49:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramakrishna is extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.31,0:49:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember Ramakrishna's state.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.31,0:49:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I went into the state that Ramakrishna described.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.31,0:49:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I went into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.31,0:49:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew Ramakrishna.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.50,0:49:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was all alone in the chapel
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.50,0:49:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,here in Sedona at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.50,0:49:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In those days they didn't lock the chapel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.66,0:49:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The music stayed on all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.66,0:49:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The candles were on all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.85,0:50:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There weren't all the tourists that there are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.85,0:50:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The chapel was unlocked at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.85,0:50:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went in there to meditate
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.85,0:50:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and went into an ecstatic state.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.17,0:50:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstatic state in which you could dance forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.17,0:50:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You could dance for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.17,0:50:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The dancing was
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.05,0:50:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the exquisite joy of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.05,0:50:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the energy field of ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.05,0:50:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and it makes you tireless.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.56,0:50:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You could dance for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.56,0:50:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I danced all by myself in front of the altar
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.56,0:50:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to express my joy to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.36,0:50:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstasy. Tireless.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.36,0:50:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the state described by Ramakrishna.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.80,0:50:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Swami Ram Dass is not as well known by others,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.44,0:50:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have a number of books by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.44,0:50:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a different Sai Baba,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.44,0:50:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not Sathya.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.44,0:50:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a different Sai Baba.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.44,0:50:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lisa Sonella I met out in California.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.54,0:51:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe he was
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.54,0:51:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a psychiatrist, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.54,0:51:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrote about kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.54,0:51:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote about kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.54,0:51:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Satya Dhananda also.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.73,0:51:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to meet a number of these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.73,0:51:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So Joseph Smith, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.73,0:51:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,started the major church.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.73,0:51:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Rudolf Steiner, well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.73,0:51:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Suzuki, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.73,0:51:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,popularized Zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.92,0:51:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Suzuki is the one that really made it well known
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.92,0:51:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.92,0:51:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa is 710.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.92,0:51:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is another saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.12,0:51:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Saints, very often at higher levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.12,0:51:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,people stop being socially active.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.40,0:51:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the majority drop out of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.40,0:51:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A few manage to retain a function within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.40,0:51:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an adjustment that's hard to describe.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.50,0:51:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an adjustment that it seems to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:51:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of a divine commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.50,0:52:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a contract made prior to this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.50,0:52:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the fulfillment of this potential
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.88,0:52:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was part of the agreement,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.88,0:52:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or the contract, or the, yeah, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.38,0:52:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that, one disappears from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.15,0:52:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of the people who go over 600 leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.15,0:52:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,50%, once they reach 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.15,0:52:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.15,0:52:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you hit 600, you'll know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.15,0:52:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're invited to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.15,0:52:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like invitational freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.44,0:52:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's recurred, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.44,0:52:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of times over the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.44,0:52:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one time it happened right in the middle of a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.44,0:52:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to the end of the aisle,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.44,0:52:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the invitation to leave was very strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.44,0:52:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You could just leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.72,0:52:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you never know when it's gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.72,0:52:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether you continue on in the world or not
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.72,0:52:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is really not up to any personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.72,0:52:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody that thinks about it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.72,0:52:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and weighs the pros and cons
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.72,0:52:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and decide I will do this or that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.72,0:53:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more or less the fulfillment of a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.56,0:53:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of gratitude for divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.56,0:53:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for the awareness that has emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.56,0:53:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this awareness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.56,0:53:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of gratitude to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.56,0:53:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,one then shares that for the good of that which God loves,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.56,0:53:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which is all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.52,0:53:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.84,0:53:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We were at, did you change this thing on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.84,0:53:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.84,0:53:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.04,0:53:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.04,0:53:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We had Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.04,0:53:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We went down this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.04,0:53:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a Krishna.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.04,0:53:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I get wandering off onto various people I've met.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.04,0:53:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few of them I didn't meet, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.04,0:53:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates, I'm looking forward to rejoining.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.04,0:53:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.04,0:53:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was capable of the miraculous
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.16,0:53:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because she looked at the very pits
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.16,0:54:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lowest level at which humanity can go
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.16,0:54:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and had the heart, the courage to look it in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.42,0:54:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people can look it in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.42,0:54:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people can't even stand television or TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.42,0:54:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't even stand television depictions of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.42,0:54:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,much less look into the heart and soul of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.74,0:54:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used to see that in patients brought in,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.74,0:54:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,bound up in wet cloths and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.80,0:54:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question would arise within consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.16,0:54:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what God do you wish of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.95,0:54:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And there would be an opening of that soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.32,0:54:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,would open itself up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.32,0:54:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that second,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.32,0:54:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment had just occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.32,0:54:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could see the soul within was healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.32,0:54:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And now whether there was a social recovery or not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.32,0:55:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was irrelevant because the moment had arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.32,0:55:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.32,0:55:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what Mother Teresa did, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.32,0:55:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of these are extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.32,0:55:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Evelyn Underhill, Vivekananda, Alan Watts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.57,0:55:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The White Brotherhood, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.57,0:55:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was written about by Alice Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.31,0:55:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yaktusraya.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.31,0:55:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A well-known teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.31,0:55:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can go to the next one, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.17,0:55:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.17,0:55:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first one.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.39,0:55:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we going backwards or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.39,0:55:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.02,0:55:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I talk about these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.65,0:55:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.72,0:55:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,James Allen, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.72,0:55:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he's written a number of books written by Dove Press.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.72,0:55:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramesh Bhalsakar,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.20,0:55:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to spend some time with out in California
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.20,0:55:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,about a week or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.20,0:55:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And Eva Sand is well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.42,0:55:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wallace Black Elk.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.42,0:55:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.71,0:55:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob Bohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.71,0:56:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard Bucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.71,0:56:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This he wrote, Cosmic Consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.71,0:56:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he was a physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.71,0:56:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eric Butterworth, extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.96,0:56:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the origin of Calvinism.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.96,0:56:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Confucius.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.22,0:56:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dalai Lama, like the Pope,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.22,0:56:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates about the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.22,0:56:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the head of a world church,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.57,0:56:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't be really too high
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.57,0:56:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because all that would not be very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.57,0:56:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But 570, you're as saintly as you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.67,0:56:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and still function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.67,0:56:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Dalai Lama functions in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.67,0:56:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If he went on to 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.76,0:56:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he would disappear from society.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.21,0:56:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all well-known teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.21,0:56:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all well-known teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.21,0:56:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Meister Eckhart, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.21,0:56:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.21,0:56:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrated over 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.69,0:56:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He seems to me he gets too much into
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.69,0:56:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,discussion of the philosophy of theology
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.69,0:56:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.69,0:57:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.72,0:57:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, the reality is the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.72,0:57:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be phrased subsequent to the experiential
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.72,0:57:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than describing it first.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.72,0:57:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me the description should arise
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.59,0:57:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.59,0:57:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is to suddenly go from frozen
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.16,0:57:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with the impossibility of dancing,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.16,0:57:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.45,0:57:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All movement is spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.45,0:57:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.77,0:57:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yes, I remember the patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.77,0:57:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that come to me back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.03,0:57:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As a spiritual dancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.03,0:57:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what I did was I danced out a pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.03,0:57:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The pattern was already in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.03,0:57:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The body merely imitated the pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.37,0:57:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which preexisted the movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.66,0:57:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So it came about spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.66,0:57:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as an acting out of the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.95,0:57:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember now as a temple dancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.95,0:57:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what held in mind was not the dance steps
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.95,0:57:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like choreography.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.95,0:57:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No choreography.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.95,0:57:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness of the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.04,0:58:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I become the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.04,0:58:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like a chromosomal,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.43,0:58:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the chromosomal spiral about itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.43,0:58:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is a spontaneous event.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.49,0:58:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-linear, in other words.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.49,0:58:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.19,0:58:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Charles Fillmore.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.19,0:58:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Fillmores were very familiar with their work.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.19,0:58:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we were on the,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.35,0:58:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would call a committee of the,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.35,0:58:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, steering committee of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.18,0:58:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.31,0:58:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Unity, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.31,0:58:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.31,0:58:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness research and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.31,0:58:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get to go to Unity
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.31,0:58:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a wonderful place to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.82,0:58:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we examined the original writings of the Fillmores
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.04,0:58:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.04,0:58:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.14,0:58:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We went up in the private library.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.14,0:58:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was locked and sacrosanct.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.14,0:58:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The librarian was just sort of speechless.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.14,0:58:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She wanted us,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.14,0:58:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so she kept pulling these things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.14,0:58:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And what beautiful handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.14,0:59:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, my mind is a scrawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.14,0:59:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is like script, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.14,0:59:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful handwriting and we calibrated that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.14,0:59:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we can recapitulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.62,0:59:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm holding, okay, I'm holding,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.62,0:59:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm holding in mind calibrates over 800,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.62,0:59:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,850, 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.62,0:59:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We got about 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.75,0:59:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That as originally written by the Fillmores.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.75,0:59:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The original, if you ever get a chance to see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.84,0:59:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if they let people see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.84,0:59:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That inspiration that came out of the heart of Christianity
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.84,0:59:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,radiated out at that incredibly high level,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.55,0:59:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which they then brought down into the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.55,0:59:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.55,0:59:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So they then were able to communicate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.64,0:59:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through the world at the level of 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.00,0:59:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is comprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.00,0:59:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really communicate with the world at 900 too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.06,0:59:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.06,0:59:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So Emmett Fox, of course, is a great teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.48,1:00:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mahatma Gandhi,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.48,1:00:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we wrote about he stood off the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.48,1:00:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The British Empire at the time they confronted Gandhi
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.48,1:00:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was coming from prideful militarism
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.48,1:00:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrated about,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.54,1:00:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what it calibrated now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.54,1:00:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote it in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.54,1:00:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,190, I think, right, pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.15,1:00:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Gandhi calibrated 760.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.15,1:00:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what I mean by standing up for truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.34,1:00:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he didn't wimp out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.34,1:00:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes what's called spirituality to me
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.88,1:00:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is just wimping out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.88,1:00:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Gandhi didn't wimp out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.46,1:00:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He stood for truth against the entire British Empire,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.46,1:00:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the most powerful empire the world had ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.46,1:00:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was born, Britannia ruled the waves.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.52,1:00:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One-third of the globe was under the dominion
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.52,1:00:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.16,1:00:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And this skinny little 90-pound Indian,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.23,1:00:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they were called colored,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.23,1:01:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,stood up against the entire British Empire
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.23,1:01:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and defeated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.23,1:01:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual strength, then, is of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.85,1:01:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not wimping out.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.95,1:01:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's standing up for that which you know to be the reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.95,1:01:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So he stood up against the British Empire,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.95,1:01:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,defeated the entire British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.01,1:01:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't that knock you out?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.01,1:01:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This 90-pound skinny little guy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.01,1:01:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,knocked over the entire British Empire,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.01,1:01:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,its sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.01,1:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That was very interesting historically.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.08,1:01:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And Joel Goldsmith is an extremely well-known writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.43,1:01:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Manly Hall collected some really wonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.43,1:01:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ernest Holmes is also in religious science.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.43,1:01:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And Vernon Howard.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.65,1:01:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all very well-known names.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.39,1:02:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Aldous Huxley, the great saints, Karmapa.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.45,1:02:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I visited the Karmapa.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.45,1:02:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the presence of the Karmapa,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.45,1:02:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but did not meet him personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.89,1:02:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Gopi Krishna, of course, his story is well-known.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.89,1:02:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one of the reasons I tell people,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.89,1:02:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,don't try to force the Kundalini.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.31,1:02:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And Kriyananda, Brother Lawrence,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.31,1:02:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, is the prayer of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.31,1:02:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lawrence, it's in a little booklet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.44,1:02:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was done, I think, in the 1600s.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.56,1:02:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The practice of the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.56,1:02:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to merely be constantly conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.56,1:02:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of God within.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.56,1:02:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A very powerful little book.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.56,1:02:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And simplicity, without getting into any kind of thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.56,1:02:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,These are, of course, two are both well-known to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.60,1:02:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-linear, Vedanta, the 700s.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.60,1:02:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Burton, extremely well-known.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.60,1:02:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's Moses de Leon of Granada,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.60,1:02:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who was a rabbi at 720.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.60,1:03:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And Mukherjee, I like his name, Mukherjee,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.60,1:03:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at 475.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.60,1:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we got another slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.88,1:03:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.24,1:03:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is that the last slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.24,1:03:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.04,1:03:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we need the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.04,1:03:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two slides on spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.04,1:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We did them both?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.22,1:03:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on now, you fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.22,1:03:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go ahead then.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.83,1:03:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we were going to talk about,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.83,1:03:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, what keeps people stuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.83,1:03:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the book we're going to have out
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.83,1:03:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at our next meeting, hopefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.89,1:03:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcending the Levels of Consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.89,1:03:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan was one of the main inspirations for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.89,1:03:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, the do-it-ness, the do-it-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.89,1:03:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to write about the do-it-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.89,1:03:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we went back over the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.89,1:03:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and looked at what is holding them in place.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.89,1:03:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.89,1:03:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually they're held in attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.96,1:04:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be spiritually free means
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.96,1:04:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not at the effect of attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.12,1:04:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither attractions nor aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.12,1:04:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And attractions and aversions are to,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.12,1:04:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,predominantly to the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.76,1:04:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, no money. Health, no health.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.76,1:04:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wishing things to be different than they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.04,1:04:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So complete surrender at great depth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.04,1:04:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender at great depth
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.04,1:04:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is the letting go of all attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.04,1:04:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you are completely free.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.24,1:04:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're completely clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.24,1:04:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not run by attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.24,1:04:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.49,1:04:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,here are the general,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.49,1:04:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the attraction is in the left-hand column
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.49,1:04:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and the aversion is in the right-hand column.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.49,1:04:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people prefer control.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.48,1:04:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of giving up control is anathema.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.74,1:04:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus it brings up all kinds of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.74,1:04:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of surrendering control
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.74,1:04:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,then means
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.74,1:05:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go, having your life run by the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.99,1:05:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.99,1:05:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the presumption is that you're alive because of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.99,1:05:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the truth is you're alive in spite of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.34,1:05:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That your survival is not based on the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.44,1:05:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but the self with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.44,1:05:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the small self
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.44,1:05:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that tells you to look out
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.44,1:05:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and not run off the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.44,1:05:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because your self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.44,1:05:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is loving you to the degree that your small self
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.56,1:05:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,pays attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.56,1:05:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the big self that your small self
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.56,1:05:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,remembers to take your vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.56,1:05:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for my ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.56,1:05:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't take my vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.56,1:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's because of your big self
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.56,1:05:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that your small self remembers
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.60,1:05:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've got to take your vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.60,1:05:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the pleasure then is being in control
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.14,1:05:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.14,1:05:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,our whole society is,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.20,1:06:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all control freaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.20,1:06:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has to control everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.20,1:06:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they don't,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.46,1:06:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes them feel uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.16,1:06:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.05,1:06:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.05,1:06:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the anticipated pleasure of stuckness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.05,1:06:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is it's, it's, it's habit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.05,1:06:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.47,1:06:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's easier to hang in with what you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.47,1:06:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've been doing rather than change.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.47,1:06:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings uncertainty and strangeness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.76,1:06:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember walking out of the house
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.76,1:06:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with no food and no money.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.76,1:06:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd written, of course, the miracles that all your,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.76,1:06:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,all your needs would be provided for.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.01,1:06:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.01,1:06:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,well, so it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.01,1:06:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.01,1:06:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Around lunchtime, somebody that I knew said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.01,1:06:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,did you have lunch yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.01,1:06:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.01,1:06:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, yeah, I can't eat all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.01,1:06:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the way it went,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.01,1:06:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,around the clock, day after day.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.01,1:06:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I never,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.01,1:06:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I literally saw anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.01,1:06:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happened,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.01,1:07:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous, just constantly presented.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.01,1:07:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to stick in with,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.36,1:07:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for a feeling of control.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.36,1:07:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, familiarity and habit
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.36,1:07:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you a feeling of control.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.36,1:07:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we're uncertain about what may happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.36,1:07:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to cling to the old
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.36,1:07:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being afraid of the,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.36,1:07:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,this also seems to take effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.91,1:07:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The easy way is to stick with the old
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.91,1:07:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.91,1:07:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to hate people,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.91,1:07:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.00,1:07:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it hard?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.00,1:07:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.52,1:07:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't hard to forgive people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.52,1:07:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is the resistance,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.52,1:07:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the clinging to wanting to be right
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.52,1:07:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanting them to be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.52,1:07:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.52,1:07:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.68,1:07:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the effort is not in
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.68,1:07:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these actual steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.68,1:07:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but in overcoming the resistance to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.73,1:07:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People would rather ignore
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.73,1:07:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and not look at a problem
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.73,1:07:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.73,1:07:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because they might get upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.28,1:08:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, learn to enjoy being upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.28,1:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fun to be upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.28,1:08:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be real theatrical
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.28,1:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and do your whole thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.28,1:08:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,stamp up and down, cry.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.69,1:08:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.69,1:08:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So go ahead and be upset, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.85,1:08:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, I can't stop being upset
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.85,1:08:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tell them,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.85,1:08:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,your problem is you're not upset enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.85,1:08:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to get more upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.85,1:08:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to get more upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.85,1:08:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Cry harder, longer, gnash your teeth,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.85,1:08:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,throw yourself on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.85,1:08:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,have a tantrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.85,1:08:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Boom, boom, boom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.88,1:08:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon it runs out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.88,1:08:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It runs out.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.88,1:08:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.04,1:08:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you choose to be this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.04,1:08:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then it loses its power over you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.04,1:08:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It only has power
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.04,1:08:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when you ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.04,1:08:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignoring and resisting it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.04,1:08:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,gives it energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.04,1:08:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Disowning it, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.04,1:08:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is what we...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.17,1:08:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to disown things
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.17,1:08:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than take responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.33,1:08:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.33,1:08:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you look at what's blocking the thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.33,1:08:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the underlying feeling?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.33,1:08:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to take responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.33,1:08:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because then I would feel guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.33,1:09:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then ask yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.33,1:09:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, and why would you feel guilty?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.33,1:09:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you keep on doing it step by step
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.33,1:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually it falls apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.33,1:09:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.33,1:09:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.33,1:09:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.33,1:09:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Always own what goes on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.28,1:09:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask what's within you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.38,1:09:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hear a glass fall off the table,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.38,1:09:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the question in my mind is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.44,1:09:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what within myself is that expressing?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.44,1:09:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Take responsibility for everything that happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.36,1:09:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Something within is expressing itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.36,1:09:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,see?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.36,1:09:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea that I can't do a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.12,1:09:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of it is I won't,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.12,1:09:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've talked about
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.22,1:09:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your banister effect that you can break through the barriers the idea that I
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.66,1:09:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can't do a thing usually means that you won't since I can't let go hating so and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.08,1:10:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so if I say if we put a loaded gun to your head now could you yeah I could so
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.28,1:10:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that points out it's not that you can't it's that you won't whatever you're
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.38,1:10:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,holding you're holding because you won't let it go not because you can't anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.64,1:10:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,here think they're the victim of can't well we got one honest person we don't
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.48,1:10:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,like to take a look at the fact that we won't because it makes us feel guilty
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.38,1:10:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but you look underneath the eye why is it why is it we are saying we I can't why
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.04,1:10:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is it we say I can't so each the way you advance your consciousness as you go
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.38,1:10:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,layer by layer by layer you know because then I would feel anxiety and why would
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.40,1:10:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel
